			<div class="content" id="post-content-4859057">
									

<h1><span><span style="color: blue">Note: If you're going to introduce yourself here, please scroll down and click &quot;New Post&quot; and NOT &quot;reply&quot;, otherwise your comment will nest incorrectly!</span></span></h1>
<p>Hello, prospective site writers! It's good to see you here!</p>
<h3><span>This month's random question is: what do you think is the best kind of food to eat with friends?</span></h3>
<p>First off, a couple standard things to keep in mind as you get started towards adding your voice to the Foundation universe:</p>
<ul>
<li>Definitely read the <a href="/how-to-write-an-scp">How to Write an SCP</a> Guide and the pages in the <a href="/guide-hub">Guide Hub</a> that are relevant to your ideas!</li>
<li>Make a <a href="/sandbox">sandbox</a> page for your works in progress, reference notes, inspirational snippets, and more author things!</li>
<li>Get familiar with our three Writing Help Forums:
<ul>
<li><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-891087">Questions Desk</a></strong>: For all your questions about the writing process!</li>
<li><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-89000/help:ideas-and-brainstorming">Ideas and Brainstorming</a></strong>: For asking about concepts that you're thinking of writing up! <span style="color: blue">This is an especially important step for first-time authors!</span></li>
<li><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-50864/help:drafts-and-critiques">Drafts and Critiques</a></strong>: For reviews of your finished pieces, to see what edits need to be made to your work to make it ready for the mainlist!</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>If you're not sure what to talk about here, you can take a look at our <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-985304/how-to-write-an-intro-or-welcome">How to Write an Intro/Welcome</a> thread for ideas.</p>
<p>Feel free to respond to other new members if you find that your writing interests and/or plans overlap. The SCP wiki is a collaborative writing community, after all! You might even see some of the longtime writers here drop by with comments now and then. :)</p>
<p>Welcome to the site!</p>

